The paper deals with privacy-preserving data sharing in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep networks and adversarial attacks, which are common topics in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new framework for privacy-preserving data sharing, which involves optimization and fine-tuning, indicating that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on image classification and face recognition tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
